microstructure: disordered body-centered cubic (BCC) solid solution phase in as-cast and homogenized states
evidence: The present paper reports the microstructure, phase stability and mechanical properties of a new refractory MoNbHfZrTi high-entropy alloy. MoNbHfZrTi alloy consists of a disordered body-centered cubic (BCC) solid solution phase in as-cast and homogenized states.

microstructure: single disordered BCC phase in as-cast and as-homogenized states
evidence: MoNbHfZrTi alloy is composed of a single disordered BCC phase in as-cast and as-homogenized states. At room temperature, the alloy has high compressive yield strength of 1719 Mpa and 1575 Mpa in as-cast and as-homogenized states.
At elevated temperatures, this alloy still has high compressive yield strength (825 MPa at 1073 K, 728 MPa at 1173 K, 635 MPa at 1273 K, 397 MPa at 1373 K and 187 MPa at 1473 K)
